{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"Integrate the task-decomposition SOTA research (docs/research/task-decomposition-sota-2026.md, commit 143d5074e, ticket englacial-communal-conure/d39b) into the plan-review gate: validate each recommendation experimentally with evals FIRST, implement only behind its results gate, then dogfood in production review. Per operator direction (2026-07-15): no A/B testing - validation is eval-based (the E-gates below), post-ship observation is dogfooding via R7 instrumentation, and the approach must be clearly documented at every step.\n\n## Context\nThe report's §5 mined this store's own history: post-claim description edits on 16/505 claimed work tickets (3.2%), 15 substantive; of 8 with persisted reviews, 3 were review MISSES sharing one defect class (plan asserts a capability an existing module lacks: dc58, db7b, 5886) and 4 were advisories applied only post-claim (latency, not blindness). Small n: 3/8 identifies the defect CLASS (binomial 95% CI 9-76%), it is not a precise miss rate - child E1 re-verifies these claims before anything depends on them. §6 defines R1-R7, each with a falsifiable experiment. Implementation targets: src/rebar/llm/plan_review/ (orchestrator, det_floor.py, passes.py, criteria_routing.json), src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/ (SHARED with code-review - R5 requires the E5 non-regression gate), src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_*.md. Calibration assets in docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/ are extended, not replaced. This epic runs alongside the calibration-3 line (task relishable-ammonitic-hoverfly, story large-sleepful-needlefish); implementation children that touch criteria_routing.json/review_kernel sequence after the floor-split story to avoid file conflicts.\n\n## Success Criteria\n- Every implemented recommendation has a committed docs/experiments/ writeup showing its gate row passed before implementation; every rejected/deferred recommendation has the failing result recorded.\n- The gate ships with no blocking-FP regression: any new blocking behavior enters via overlay advisory-first, promoted only per the rollout discipline (monitor via R7 FP proxy, alarm >10% trailing, demote-on-alarm precedent T3/T10).\n- The plan-review methodology remains documented: docs/plan-review-gate.md reflects every landed change.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] E1 ground-truth corpora are frozen and committed under docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/ with a versioned README (outcome corpus + finding-adjudication corpus, inter-rater kappa >= 0.7 recorded).\n- [ ] Each experiment child (E1, E2, E3, E5, E6) is closed with its results recorded as ticket comments AND a docs/experiments/ writeup.\n- [ ] Each recommendation child (R1-R7) is either landed through Gerrit with its gate row demonstrably passed, or closed/deferred with the failing gate result recorded - no recommendation implemented without its gate.\n- [ ] All landed criteria/rubric changes follow the rollout discipline (overlay advisory-first, R7 monitoring documented) and docs/plan-review-gate.md is updated to match."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784143650755702001,"uuid":"3e5904b8-3001-465d-8603-91ad9ff0c65e"}